"RATES OF CONSUMPTION PER CAPITA PER COUNTRY:

Once human beings experience electricity, running water, and
telephones, they want more of them, no matter what the cost to
the environment.  Would we - do we? - behave differently?
According to one calculation, the average Amercian baby
represents thirty-five times the future enviornmental damage of
an Indian child.  The United States consistently heads the list of
countries with the highest greenhouse gas emissions,
including twice the CFCS 9 (choloroflourocarbons), of its nearest
competitor.  And after a brief period of conservation, we are again  using
energy as if it were limitless."

-Mary Settegast, "MONA LISA'S MOUSTACHE, Making Sense of a
Dissolving World," p. 38.

Subject: [sfraves] POLICE BRUTALITY CAUSED DEATH AT MUSIC FESTIVAL CZECHTEK

--=====================_2268968==.ALT
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"; format=flowed

<<POLICE BRUTALITY CAUSED DEATH ON MUSIC FESTIVAL CZECHTEK

for immediate release

Czechtek is open-air international and multicultural music festival 
with 12 year tradition. Not only different genres of music, but also 
videoart and other art performances take place on this unique event 
of free culture.

In all history of festival there were no significant damages or 
problems, participants while leaving clean the land and take 
responsibility for their action.

Contract with the owner of grass plain was clearly shown to police. 
There is no indicaion that festival was in any way illegal, every 
aspect was according to law of Czech Republic.

Although police stated throughout friday 29th several different 
reasons for blockage of access to the place of festival, all were 
later shown as lies or desinformation. The final reason for brute 
attack was \"threat of damaging the surrounding private pieces of land\".

The presence of attending young people on surrounding land was caused 
by police blockage of all roads and the police action was not taken 
against this people, but against the people on legally borrowed property.

Woman from near willage, owner of adjoining land, said she had been 
woken up by police friday morning, long before people began to 
arrive, taken to police station and by false arguments encouraged to 
sign complaint.

Most of the people did not hear any appeal to leave the place, many 
of them had drunk alcohol-containing beverages and could not go away 
with cars, many of them believed that by taking part on legally 
organized festival they cannot be targeted by police.

The first police action on saturday 30, 16:30PM took several hours 
and was badly coordinated. On the place was 1000 policemen, water 
cannon, armoured tank and low-flying helicopter.

The second night attack at 22PM was led with extreme brutality.

Police in heavy suits without identifying numbers refused to give 
identifying information, information about their command and 
information about first aid location.

Police used massive amounts of tear gas and desorientation grenades, 
in many cases they threw tear gas granade into a car and did not let 
people inside for long time get out, in other cases they broke car 
windows by iron bars, threw grenade in and forced people to get out.

All people were beaten up, including teenage girls, which cried in 
pain. Witnesses described attack on lone staing girl, who was pulled 
down by her hair and kicked on the ground by four policemen.

There were hundreds of injuries, including cuts, bruises, burnings, 
broken arms, shock. Many people were in shock still the next day 
afternoon with red faces from tear gas.

Police intentionally damaged cars, electronic equipment and other 
property. Attack was led with clear intention to cause injuries.

People were forced to go to near highway, which was closed several 
hours and then the waiting trucks were allowed to go dangerously 
among the desoriented people. Police confirmed death of young man 
attending the festival. Reportedly he was killed by truck which left. 
The reason of this death can be manipulated by police, no wittnesses 
were found to confirm police statement.

Police brutality continued on scattered people till the sunday morning.

Czech state television Czech TV did not inform about the night 
attack, it\'s news were not balanced, mainly repeating police 
statements. Czech TV in its news also under estimated political value 
of call of freedom and resignation of minister of interior on 
sunday\'s demonstration in Prague, reporting briefly about techno-goers.

This is a call to foreing media to publish information about unlawful 
police brutality and state of democracy and human rights in Czech Republic.

press release of the visions.cz server, 31. 7. 23:30>>

And more:

http://www.indymedia.org/en/2005/07/118313.shtml






Moksha Tribe:  www.mokshatribe.org

House Music 101:  http://livingart.com/raving/articles/housemusic101.htm

"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"



--=====================_2268968==.ALT--

What is Spin THIS! ?
Spin THIS!: A Nite of Dark Elektronix is the event showcase of the  
Dark-Tekno Collective and other talented musicians, DJs, performers, and
artists. The music featured varies the breadth of electronic music,  
emphasizing the dark side- danceable Power Noize, Psy-Trance,  
Industrial, Dark Techno, Drum & Bass,IDM, Breaks, Dark Jungle,  
Digital Hardcore, Dark Electro, etc ...

SAT AUG 6TH is the next Spin THIS!  We are having our own Mutant  
Night!  So come dressed as a freaky Mutant! CD & Goody Giveaways to  
people in costume (while they last- first come, first served!)!   
Dance to slamming beats on the main floor and chill to awesome live  
acts and downtempo/ambient/IDM DJs  upstairs.  Performers of wonder  
and whimsy are candy for the eyes AND mind.

Subject: Re: [sfraves] NRR: The Maker of the Atkiens diet went bankrupt!

That's not true unless you have joint accounts or
family members have secured some of the debt using
their personal assets.  The debt does get passed on to
your estate however.  Consult an attorney for advice
on estate planning to protect your ass(ets) upon your
demise.

Peter

Subject: [sfraves] BSP: 9-2: Roni Size - 1015: EK's 8 yr old BDay Shindig!

Just thought I'd post this on here 2 give y'all in SFR land a month's
notice in advance so U can plan your Groovy on... 'cause ya know... w/o
the added support of the Hardcore Junglists Ravers in the Bay Area...
well... then EK wouldn't be what it is in the melting pot of the Awesome
dance scene it's part of!

To view flyer & thread:

http://www.groundscore.net/board/viewtopic.php?t=13569&postdays=0&postorder=asc&start=0

Eklektic Turns 8 / Fuck Off And Dance

What began in 1997 as three girls' party-with-heart, San Francisco's
infamous Eklektic, lived up to its name for the five years that it ran as
a weekly. A drum & bass night at the core, Eklektic developed to involve
everything from dub to disco to hip hop to 'ardcore to 2- step to breaks.

With a strong foundation in local talent and tough rank of residents,
Eklektic and its production company, Groundscore, brought top-shelf sounds
to a warm and enthusiastic reception in the "red light district" of their
dancefloor.

There are few headliners who have yet to grace the decks over the years as
the party has lived on as a series of one-offs. Roni Size, however, is one
of them, and September 2 marks Eklektic's 8 Year Anniversary by showcasing
the one who can truly reprazent. Groundscore welcomes the opportunity to
introduce one unmistakable vibe to another. Not to be missed!

Eklektic's 8 Year Anniversary with Roni Size, Gridlok, 4Real, Mal, Audio
Angel, MCs Duh & Colonel, Felix the Dog, Rascue, and Jamin. September 2,
2005 / Doors open at 10pm / 1015 Folsom at 6th St.


Keep Your Ear To The Ground!
--------------------------------------------->
WE AREN'T FRONTIN'. EKLEKTIC's 8 YR. SOIREE'->9.2.05

I like this quote from the Czech PM:


The Czech president criticised the crackdown, but Prime Minister Jiri 
Paroubek said techno fans were "no dancing children but dangerous people".

Writing in the Lidove noviny newspaper on Tuesday, he said the core 
of the techno enthusiasts was made up of "obsessed people with 
anarchist proclivities and international links," who "provoke massive 
violent demonstrations, fuelled by alcohol and drugs, against the 
peaceful society".

"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"

for somebody that sat atop a multi-million empire that purported to sell=20
good health, Atkins was a fucking mess wasn't he?

that about sums it up, good job.

caloric restriction is the way to go, but you have to lose the idea that=20
it's about pounds or weight because it isn't.

It's about gaining days, and living longer, not about the yo-yo hamster=20
wheel trip that passes for dieting in the USA.

In a nutshell, the concept of caloric restriction is that if you cut your=
=20
caloric intake by a third, you'll live a third longer.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caloric_restriction

however it's not as much as a sell-able sell as mad-cap American dieting=20
since for one thing, were this to take hold, the populace would be eating=
=20
and buying less food and if that was happening that not only would the=20
agriculture industries take a major financial hit, but mass media=20
advertising would also see significant drops in gross revenue, since if=20
people aren't buying as much Coke & Pepsi as they used to, then Coke and=20
Pepsi won't have the monies they have to day to fritter away on Superbowl=
=20
spots.

More money in keeping the population on the road to illness than there is=
=20
pursuing long term good health.

nwa

--- party nfos <raves@wayfar.net> wrote:

> Well, if it's possible to get 20-30 db in channel seperation then
> that 
> should be good enough, I'm curious so I'll just prepare a test
> recording 
> and get a dub at Richard Simpson mastering and check the results,

The other impediment to this idea that I haven't seen spoken of here is
that you'd need a fairly complex mixer setup to do this right- either:

Turntable L and R -> 
Standalone phono preamp to get the signal to line level -> 
Each side goes into a mono channel strip on a standard (non-dj) mixer
(repeat for each turntable)

...thus making the setup a pain to drag with you to a gig, or

Turntable L and R -> 
Sketchy RCA splitters to create new L/R pairs from each output -> 
Two standalone stereo phono preamps -> 
Two separate stereo line ins on the dj mixer  
(repeat for each table)

...thus forcing you to only play on large-capacity club mixers, and to
savage the setup of any venue you play at in a way that would take
quite a while to reverse in the dark!

I hate to discourage what is quite a cool idea academically, but
Ableton Live/Final Scratch/Serato Scratch/Traktor/et al might just be a
better idea at this point.  That, or maybe go Richie Hawtin-style and
press individual elements on their own tracks on vinyl, rock
doubles/triples/quads and build build build..  

This just seems like a lot of torment to go through for the the ability
to have two parts playing in sync from a single record, m'thinks.

Please post examples of you playing with it if you go through with it,
though! :)

-george cochrane | origami
-newstylesound recordings
-djorigami.com
-foldedsf.com

-&e->> >don't allow you to "pan" or control the left/right
-&e->> >balance so it wouldn't be easy to mix the L/R
-&e->> channels
-&e->> >this way...
-&e->> >
-&e->> >Peter
-&e->> >
-&e->> >--- party nfos <raves@wayfar.net> wrote:
-&e->> >
-&e->> >  
-&e->> >
-&e->> >>Hi,
-&e->> >>
-&e->> >>Just wondering how many of you own, or how much a
-&e->> >>specific genre uses 
-&e->> >>the L/R channels on the vinyl as seperate tracks,
-&e->> >>that way you can not 
-&e->> >>only mix between records but between pannings on
-&e->> the
-&e->> >>records.
-&e->> >>

than any location in the Bay Area.  With a decor of Indian and middle
eastern influences, a sound system of the highest caliber, a vip area of
sultan status, and a line-up of the best house djs in the bay area will

JASK (Thai Soul)

The Blue Monkey is located at 1 E San Fernando Street, SJ 21+.

"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"

Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"; format=flowed


It's time once again to come together in the most beautiful 
celebration in the world: Bang The Drum, as we celebrate 21 years of 
Hip-Hop Radio!!!!

It happens Sunday, August 21st at Casino Meadow, outdoors in San 
Francisco's Golden Gate Park.   From 1PM -5PM, 21 MCs and 21 DJs will 
bless the stage in celebration of the 21st Anniversary of The 
Drum.  For those of you who missed last year's event, this is your 
chance to realign w/the universe. . .for those who were there, you 
know what time it is.  Featuring a B-Boy/B-Girl showcase, Graf 
exhibition, and Beatbox wizardry, this event is Free and open to all 
ages. . .so bring your family, folks, and peoples.

Mark it down on your calendars, spread the word, and prepare 
yourself:  It's time to Bang The Drum!!!


[]




MySpace:  http://www.myspace.com/DJApollo

Tribenet: 
<http://people.tribe.net/djapollo2k>http://people.tribe.net/djapollo2k

Moksha Tribe:  www.mokshatribe.org

House Music 101:  http://livingart.com/raving/articles/housemusic101.htm



"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"

--=====================_15943015==.ALT

Subject: [sfraves] BSP: Newish mix out...

Ok, so the one and only Mr.Jack Triumph has a show on Frisky Radio, and he 
asked me to hook him up with a mix for the show. So I dug out a lil' 
somethin' I did at the end of last year, and with the help of a friend, 
fixed the levels and now have somethin' to begin distributing to you folks 
in the upcoming weeks...

It's a short mix, coming in at just under an hour, but it bangs pretty hard 
despite the brevity of it.

Tracklisting:

1. Creative Invasion Collective - Co Num Drum - BoomBox
2. Aquasky vs. Masterblaster - Cobra (Baitercell & Schumacher mix) - 
Passenger
3. DB - That Thing (Koma & Bones mix) - Distinctive
4. Lee Coombs & Dylan Rhymes - Alright All Night - Finger Lickin'
5. Splitloop - Klaxx (Introspective mix) - Sinister
6. Elite Force - Driving Me Crazy - TCR
7. Koma & Bones - Questo y Sporco - TCR
8. Pod & Bowser - The Anti - Vinyl Addiction
9. Plump DJs - How Much Is Enough? - Finger Lickin'
10. Scam - Hot 4 U - Deepcut

It'll be BRIEFLY up on my GF's site in MP3 format...I'm trying to keep the 
downloads to a minimum for her. After that, I'll have it available in single 
track CDAudio format (so you fuckers HAVE to listen to the whole mix).

You know the drill - holla if'n you want one!!

Marc(O)
*THWAP!*//Moksha Tribe//Mario Bros.
DC/MD/VA/CA

Shop. Created in the minds of M3, Loren, Rick Preston, and Mark Johns, The
Velvet Shop, to date has been the most successful underground platform of
the South Bay. Over the past 11 years, Mark Johns and M3 have brought in
some of the top tier DJs of the electronic music industry. Miguel Migs,
Mark Farina, David Harness, Ellen Ferrato, and Julius Papp have all graced
the tables at this venue.  Check out The Velvet Shop every Thursday at The
Sofa Lounge on 372 South First Street in Downtown San Jose.

11:00PM Jay Vigor vs Influence
12:00PM Aaron Jae vs M.O.D
1:00PM Greg J
2:00PM Donna Matrix
3:00pm Cantos vs Undecided

more info: SFBreaks.org=20

from Nitevibe.com:
A rogue band of local DJs, most of them previously unaffiliated with
one another, have created Bay 2 Breakin', a vehicle of representation
for our underground breaks scene in this year's upcoming Love Parade.
Powered solely by love and enthusiasm for the sound and scene, the
first product of B2B's DIY operation will surface this week when their
first bass-lauding beat session goes off at Shadow Lounge. On the
decks they'll have DJs Greg J, Donna Matrix, and Erik Hz, to mention
but a few, and with them mixing and scratching up the fresh, funky
cuts all dirty-like, you'll be showing them mad love by nights end.
Throw in some cash too - there's alot more bassy breaks where this is
coming from.
--=20

"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"

Mayor declares August 10th as House Unity Day in Chicago


The Mayor of Chicago, Richard M Daley, issued a proclamation 
declaring August 10th as House Unity Day in Chicago. House legends 
such as Frankie Knuckles, Jesse Saunders, Marshall Jefferson, Paul 
Johnson, and Mickey Oliver are cited as among the many who came 
together to celebrate House Unity Day at Summerdance in the Peace 
Garden at Grant Park.

Friday, August 5, 2005 ** Machine Drome3 **

Fri 8/5 9:00 PM $7 Tenderloft [142 Taylor St. (betw/ Turk & Eddie) The=20
City] Drum Machine Museum Presents Machine Drome Featuring Seamus Cater=20
(Holland)Redcat Theater & Roddy Schrock

Friday, Aug 5 2005 9:00 PM Tenderloft 142 Taylor St. (betw/ Turk & Eddie)=
=20
The City

Seamus Cater and Roddy Schrock will be doing a collaberation with found=20
sounds and super collider. The Event will also feature Drum Machine=20
residents LX Rudis & Chris Fleeger, Cypod and DJ Guanaco

Seamus Cater is an English musician and composer living in Amsterdam,=20
Holland. His musical output encompasses both the acoustic and the=20
electronic, often combining the two. Equally at home in the studio and as=
=20
performer, his work is produced using rigorous and complex means where the=
=20
product is deceptively simple. He works extensively with numerous=20
international choreographers composing for modern dance works, sometimes=20
performing scores real-time. Recent projects have included documentary=20
film scores and installations in art galleries. As a laptop improvisor he=
=20
collaborates internationally in two new electro-acoustic improvisation=20
groups, 'Hills not Skyscrapers' and 'Afrouzeh'. www.seacater.com

Roddy Schrock (b. 1976) is a sound artist who digitally mines the profound=
=20
from everyday sound and canvasses the glitzy, rough edges of pop for its=20
articulate immediacy. He has lived and worked in Tokyo, Holland, and New=20
York. He completed graduate studies at Mills College under the tutelage of=
=20
Alvin Curran and John Bischoff, with post-graduate work at the Royal=20
Conservatory of the Hague in the Netherlands. His music has been presented=
=20
at the Kunstvlaai Festival (Amsterdam), ShoboShobo (Tokyo), Music at the=20
Anthology (New York), Sonic Circuits (Washington DC), Ostrava New Music=20
Days (Czech Republic), and the CEAIT Festival (Los Angeles). He has also=20
performed at many intimate galleries, cafes, bars, and even a planetarium.=
=20
He is based in San Francisco and teaches SuperCollider software at STEIM=20
(Netherlands) in the summer. fundamentallysound.org


Cost : $7=20
http://www.hyperreal.org/raves/sf/calendar2/events/view?identifier=3D2170=
=20
San Francisco California, USA

keep this rocking $5 at the door Premium sound, lights and vibes. Rotating=

trance, hard dance and NRG. No Weapons, No Drugs & No Drama, Respect the=20

THE INTERGALACTIC SHOWDOWN In the Milky Way Saloon

The Doramey Fossillotti, an ancient alien race living in a solar system=20
just outside of our galaxy, are converging on our planet soon. They have=20
openly invited all beings to take part in an intergalactic celebration and=
=20

is clean and safe and kept up to code. 18+ / Full bar for 21+

Saturday, August 6, 2005 ** Spin THIS! Out of this world! **

What is Spin THIS! ? Spin THIS!: A Nite of Dark Elektronix is the event=20
showcase of the Dark-Tekno Collective and other talented musicians, DJs,=20
performers, and artists. The music featured varies the breadth of=20
electronic music, emphasizing the dark side- danceable Power Noize,=20
Psy-Trance, Industrial, Dark Techno, Drum & Bass,IDM, Breaks, Dark Jungle,=
=20
Digital Hardcore, Dark Electro, etc ...

SAT AUG 6TH is the next Spin THIS!  We are having our own Mutant Night!=20
So come dressed as a freaky Mutant! CD & Goody Giveaways to people in=20
costume (while they last- first come, first served!)!  Dance to slamming=20
beats on the main floor and chill to awesome live acts and=20
downtempo/ambient/IDM DJs upstairs.  Performers of wonder and whimsy are=20
candy for the eyes AND mind.

We are also pleased as punch to present- THE UNWOMAN OFFICIAL RELEASE=20

Friday, August 12, 2005 ** Moxie **

MOXIE. We want to pump you up!

Moxie's the sister party to (and impetus for) the Moxie Musik radio show=20
Sundays 9-11pm on WAR 93.7fm/westaddradio.com.  Enthusiasm is encouraged=20
for this gathering of like-minded, hyphee boogie-mongers.  (Not=20
booger-mongers, thx.)  Genres can be mis-leading, so we made our own:=20
techlectro, a mish-mash of electrohaus, techno, tech-house, and (the=20
=FCber-bastard) rocktronica.

Fact is, we play fun music -- like REALLY fun -- and whatever we may be,=20
we are never being boring. (We dressed up and fought, then thought: make=20
amends. And we were never holding back or worried that time would come to=
=20
an end.)  We ride the cusp of new music while pulling out those ol' gems=20
and classics that express the kind of funk and synth revelry we so enjoy,=
=20
just so we can play for you!

August 12 special DJs are Solar, Baby Ryan, Animal Style & Qzen.  So pull=
=20
on your fun boots, and come jam with us!

More music in your pants, Moxie loves you!=20

THE SFRaves.org Calendar is sent via email every week.

To subscribe to the list, send a message to:
sfraves-calendar-subscribe@hyperreal.org

To remove your address from the list, send a message to:
sfraves-calendar-unsubscribe@hyperreal.org

Send mail to the following for info and FAQ for this list:
sfraves-calendar-info@hyperreal.org or sfraves-calendar-faq@hyperreal.org

If you have events to add to the SFRaves calendar, please publish them by
Friday @ Noon to be included in the SFR Calendar Weekly Edition Mailing.

SFRaves is a not for profit entity serving the Bay Area & all forms of
electronic music for 13 years.

--0-101107746-1123311585=:69187
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii

Subject: [sfraves] WR... SO far... Thursday night.. Ruby Skies

OK... so Thursday night after class.. I went 2 Ruby Skies after class...
mind U IU leave 2 go 2 school from my house around like 3:30 PM - 4:30 PM
& have class 6-9:30~10PM... so I wasn't able 2 check my SFR email or GS
Board about the mondo DJ changes that went on well... after DJ Craze...

anywaze.. got in 2 the club.. 1st timne.. really nice!!!  But seriously
man.. they need more wooden floor & it sucks tryin' 2 dance on Lynolium
crap floor!!  But Kuze was on.... he started out the night right... nice,
hard, & yummy Jungle... perfect 4 after class & walkin' around SOMA 'til I
finally got there.. LoL!!!  OH oh oh... when i 1st got in the club... I
got in the main room & from where iw as standing in the back like scopin'
out the room.. LoL.. what looked like this 10 yr old kid hoppin around on
stage & yelling in2 this mic.. LoL.. oh shit.. Hello 2day.. it was MC
Child!!  YAY!!!  So I went up closer... he yelled my name on the mic &
said Hello 2Day... LoL... he came down & we hugged each other this mondo
hug 'cause seriouisly.. it's been like 2 months since we hung out & we
missed each other.. YAY!!!

OK.. on next were the Bacholers of Science.. again... I missed these fools
also!!  I only see them like 2 times a year if that.. so it was a nice
reunion w/ them 2 also!!!  YAY!!  OK.. so they kinda went a level down
from the hard shit & got really dubby I guess with their set!!!  it was
YUmmy non the less... OH my gosh.. they played alota tracks they produced
also!!! OH my goodness man.. Hello 2day.. they dropped a track they made
featuring Audio Angel.... OOOOOOOOOOOh.. I was in Heaven when i was on the
dfance floor!!

it was by this point in the night when I started drinking.. & y'all know
how i am when I drink & I'm somewhere where i wanna dance... la la la...

So it was about this time when the mini Democratic convention finally got
out & the upstairs room finally opened & Evil Breaks threw it down
hardcore man... I Loved it!!!  OK.. so briefly: Aaron Jaemon went all
future breaks, DJ Bam threw down the funky & old skool & prgressive...
MODie got busy w/ the chll breaks.. well.. IMO... it was fun though & I
did find myself up there alot.. getting really drunk... Hello 2day!

OK... back downstairs... DJ M went on after Bachlors... YAY!!!  He was all
keepin' it kinda dunny i guess... then Photek went on.. Oooooooh my gosh..
Loved his set!!  Oh yeah.. Armani was Sick when he was MCing... diff
flava.. Loved it!!!  But yeah... I teased Photek afterwards that his set
was better than the set in May @ 1015... LoL... & I was all tellin' him
that he looked less confuzed that he did.. LoL

It was a totally good night... I waxz getting pissed @ the wallflowers who
were just hoggi'n up space @ the club... I mean.. I dunno... it was
probably just drunk thoughts
but man... it was a good night!!  LoL.. yeah.. afterwards went 2 a mini
kinda after party dealie @ some1's hotel room &  hella talked 2 Photek..
LoL.. it was fun!!!  YAY

Thaks DJ M 4 a Dope night!!!

Subject: [sfraves] Friday night: LoL... ShadowLounge, ANU, 1015, Pizza, & DNA

So lastnight was a last minute adventure that Mz Adrianna Kitty kinda set
upwell... we planned on goin' out throughout the week... so she picked  me
up... Oh.. I didn't leave the cordles phone in my pocket this time...

So we got 2 Shadowlounge... ummm... ok.. BigDude was on the decks, spun
this like future breaks set.. oh oh oh oh oh oh... met up w/ Steve
Heeeeeeeeeelloooooooooooooosteen 2Day (Steve Osteen) finally like IRL
kinda dealie @ Shadow... LoL... fun guy!!  SO us 3 kinda kicked it the
whole night... but ok.. so like the other Breaks sets @ Shadow were dope..
i don't ooh oh oh... Marco spun a sickj set also1!!  YAY!! but I dunno we 
kinda cut out b4 Aaron Jaemon's set & Greg J's set... ooops... & went 2
Anu!!

@ Anu.. it was Dope... Family Reunion of sorts 4 me 2 C mondo Family there
4 AP & Origami's night!!  YAY!!!  So Dope!!  LoL.. ummm.. there as this
old 80's tune the Andrew dropped over some yumy house.. I 4got wehat song
it was though... hmmm... but yeah.. andrew spinning, live Sax... (right) &
live bass... LOVE IT!!!  So muh fun!!!

Oh yeah.. we did go 2 Lit 4 a while so i could say HI 2 my Girl Jen who
was @ the bar... YAY.. it was a hip hop thingie there!

then we got 2 1015 & LoL.. well.. Foward is usually a Dope as party.. but
there weren't that many people there this time around 4 Foward..
interesting... but it was still fun.. Oh my goodness man.. so were dancing
in the main room.. this idiot DJ played this yummy proggy house track &
the needle skipped... TWICE... it's like WTF man.. you're in the main room
fo 1 of the biggest clubs in SF, World reknown & shit, & U got a shitty
vinayl that has scratches.. WTF!!!

So it wasn't 2 long 'til after thaat we left... ohoh oh.. so it was this
"benefit" thingie & like the front room was lke Hip Hop & Reggae & some
dude rapping & beat boxing... but yeah... it was honestly kinda lame
there.. but i did C some peopel who I Love & they kinda saved me while i
was there!!  YAY!!!

Then we went 2 DNA & luckily, I got us in there... LoL... ummm.. yeah...
so like it was fun... I mean.. i was tiiiiiiiiiired from like waking u
earlier yesterday nmorning & shit & hmmm... daned a fuckin' marathon by
that point... la la la... anywaze.. it was the makers of Remedy who have a
new weekly there @ DNa on Friday's.. same crowd... it was fun,,, LoL..
even when i went 2 the back room 7 used the computer & talkedon IRC 2 my
Homies in London, Oregan, & Canada!  LoL

But it was a fun night!!  I liked hangin' out w/ Steve.. you're fuckin'
Dope Dude!!!  & as always... Adriana help me celebrate the 1hyperness of
the night & silly shit & YAY!!!  LoL.. Lvoe U Girl1!!

Apperetnly, 2night will be another adventure!!!  Sooooooo, we'll see what
happens!!!  YAY!!!  Hello 2day.. I'm so fuckin hyper right now... LoL..
Hello 2day.. hope y'all havin' a Groovy weekend & be safe!!!

---------------------------------------------------------------------

For additional commands, e-mail: sfraves-help@hyperreal.org

Subject: [sfraves] BONQWOCK--> Saturday night Adventure w/ Mz Kitty & computers!

OK... so we started the night out this Prog night hosted by the Aura Sf
crew @ Alpha Bar in the Richmond in the City... It was fun.. got there &
kicked it w/ Koroma.. OK.. hello 2day.. that place is pretty shwank
actually... nice size dnace floor, big ass TV area & big screen TV... an
old school arcade game in the corner.. !!!FOOD SERVED ALL NIGHT!!!  OK.. &
Hello 2Day.. COMPUTERS!!! LOLOLMAO.. OK..I totally geeked out 4 like an
hour like when i got my food & I IRCed from a computer & talk 2 my Homies
who were on in the #dnbradio channel... Oh My Gosh man... I'm such a dork!
 But it was fun!

OK.. so here's who spun... OK.. I don't remember his name.. but DJ #1 spun
this Awesome Prog House set mixed w/ some Tech House & some Disco house as
well oooh oh oh.. & some Breaks!!  YUM!!

Floorcraft went on next & like totally well.. ok.. his set started out
reeeeeally medicore & not like weak.. but there wasn't uuummmph, ya know? 
But but but.. midway.. OK.. I totally remember this.. he spun this like
total house mondo heavy on the electro track & even though I was still
IRCing from the computer... it totally tickled my ear & I was just WOW...
& his set got really up & just Mondo YUM after that!  I mean... I danced
alot during the last part of his set... he throew down & I told him..
Dude.. that was sick towards the end man!!  My fave set from him thous
far.. well.. th 2nd part...

Oh oh oh.. so yeah.. in the guys bathroom... when i was peeing in the ice
filled urinal.. there were these boobs talkin' 2 me while i pee'd.. Honest
2 God & Yaya.. so I wasn't drunk or high sweetie!!  But yeah... I dunno if
any other guys ever say that on this list.. but yeah.. honest 2 God..
Boobs were talkin' 2 me while I pee'd!!!

Oh yeah... it was CooL man. 'cause I saw like hella people @ the bar who I
ain'tseen in a long time!!  So that was refeshing reconecting w/ people
again!

OK.. Forest went on & I was really lookin' foward 2 her set 'cause I had a
feeling she was gonna bust out electro.. but I dunno.. night was still
young & the underground was calling our names... so after a mondo totally
hug w/ forest & itty bitty catch up talk... me & Adrianna said Bye & went
well... 2 our 2nd home!

the location was Dope.. Loved it!! I mean.. this was primarily a breaks
underground, but 2 my surprise.. there was an upstairs that had Jungle &
Hello 2day... Push was on the decks spinning fuckin' Old School Dub &
vocals & I was fuckin' eating it up & dancing in there the whole night
well.. as long as Push was spinning.. Kuze came on next & well.. I had my
Kuze fill on Thursday night... so I was wasn't in that room that much @
that point.. but he stilled played a Groovy set!  YAY!!

I wasn't in the breaks rtoom that much... but from what i heard &
occasionally grooved 2 in passing... it was sets full of Future, New
School, & Funky breaks!  Loved it!!

The energy, the vibe in the whole palce was Awesome!!  OH my gosh man.. so
Dope!!!  Like I eman... ummm.. naw man.. it was just sICK!!  Loved it!! 
The breaks Main room was flooded w/ so much good energy w/ people dancing
& it was Dope!!!  Every1 there was just WOW!!!  Loved it!!

It was Dope too 'caUSE WEll.. I saw ALOOOOOOOOOT of people there who I
ain't seen in sooooooooooooooooo long!  I mean.. seriously.. it was
Awesome, so Dope!!!  Like I mean... ok.. yeah.. again... I was havin' a
fuckin' Groovy time & that added 2 it 2 C people I've missed!!!!  Oh MY
Gosh man.. I even saw ROCKY!!  Literally man.. 1 of the only people who I
started goin' 2 Raves w/ back in the day who was working @ the bar... I
mean.. y'all know how much I Love this Dude 'cause ooh man.. so muych good
energy & out brohood hasn't even like it's still there if not even
stronger!

Oh yeah... Max McDuhster... I Love U!!  U fuckin' Asshole :P  LOLOLMAO..
Hello 2day.. yeah.. fun stuff man!  U dork... there's you're Love message!
 LOLOLOLMAO

But man... this rave was a totally throwback 2 where I came from..
seriously man... LOVED IT!!!  YAY!!!  Oh my gosh man.. so dope!  I"m so
fuckin' riculously after party high right now!!  LOLOLOLMAO

YAY!!!  Wow... So Dope!!!  LOLOLOLMAO... OK.. y'all know how I am about my
Raves & stuff.. but man.. this rates as 1 if the top #3 raves I been 2
this year!!  YAY!!!

-- 
Take Care <3
Peace=->Jus' Me =-> O§bY {8O)

If you're running on Mac Tiger OS, just download the "Osby to English  
Translator" widget. (In the info pane, you can also set it to Queen's  
English in which case his name appears as "Ousbee" and randomly adds  
little tags such as "Jolly good" and "Cheers.") Just below that is  
listed the "Geri Dahl Abstract Prose Composer" widget in case you  
need a fix, and right after that is the "Delurification Probe" widget  
which activates the secret SFR spyware in all list subscriber  
computers & allows you to see the precise location of any lurkers on  
a real-time GPS satellite map.

Subject: [sfraves] RONI SIZE @ 1015; EK's 8 YR BDAY!!!

To view flyer & thread:

http://www.groundscore.net/board/viewtopic.php?t=13569&postdays=0&postorder=asc&start=0

Eklektic Turns 8 / Fuck Off And Dance

What began in 1997 as three girls' party-with-heart, San Francisco's
infamous Eklektic, lived up to its name for the five years that it ran as
a weekly. A drum & bass night at the core, Eklektic developed to involve
everything from dub to disco to hip hop to 'ardcore to 2- step to breaks.

With a strong foundation in local talent and tough rank of residents,
Eklektic and its production company, Groundscore, brought top-shelf sounds
to a warm and enthusiastic reception in the "red light district" of their
dancefloor.

There are few headliners who have yet to grace the decks over the years as
the party has lived on as a series of one-offs. Roni Size, however, is one
of them, and September 2 marks Eklektic's 8 Year Anniversary by showcasing
the one who can truly reprazent. Groundscore welcomes the opportunity to
introduce one unmistakable vibe to another. Not to be missed!

Eklektic's 8 Year Anniversary with Roni Size, Gridlok, 4Real, Mal, Audio
Angel, MCs Duh & Colonel, Felix the Dog, Rascue, and Jamin. September 2,
2005 / Doors open at 10pm / 1015 Folsom at 6th St.


Keep Your Ear To The Ground!
--------------------------------------------->
WE AREN'T FRONTIN'. EKLEKTIC's 8 YR. SOIREE'->9.2.05

Subject: [sfraves] nrr I.C.E

i thought this was a really helpful thing to
have...just passin' on da good word:)


http://www.hoax-slayer.com/ice-campaign-email.html

http://www.eastanglianambulance.com/content/news/newsdetail.asp?newsID=646104183

East Anglian Ambulance Service have launched a
national "In case of Emergency (ICE)" campaign with
the support of Falklands war hero Simon Weston and in
association with Vodafone's annual life savers award.

The idea is that you store the word "I C E" in your
mobile phone address book, and against it enter the
number of the person you would want to be contacted
"In Case of Emergency". In an emergency situation
ambulance and hospital staff will then be able to
quickly find out who your next of kin are and be able
to contact them. It's so simple that everyone can do
it.

It may be a hoax in England, but it ain't here; my public health  
nurse says paramedics and others look for and use this info when they  
find someone with a cell phone who can't otherwise respond.

On Aug 10, 2005, at 12:03 PM, Delia wrote:

> i thought this was a really helpful thing to
> have...just passin' on da good word:)
>
>
> http://www.hoax-slayer.com/ice-campaign-email.html
>
> http://www.eastanglianambulance.com/content/news/newsdetail.asp? 
> newsID=646104183
>
> East Anglian Ambulance Service have launched a
> national "In case of Emergency (ICE)" campaign with
> the support of Falklands war hero Simon Weston and in
> association with Vodafone's annual life savers award.
>
> The idea is that you store the word "I C E" in your
> mobile phone address book, and against it enter the
> number of the person you would want to be contacted
> "In Case of Emergency". In an emergency situation
> ambulance and hospital staff will then be able to
> quickly find out who your next of kin are and be able
> to contact them. It's so simple that everyone can do
> it.

"No sage or savior has even endorsed greed and gluttony as a path 
toward social justice or personal fulfillment.  These sane and 
enlightened people come to us from all cultures and all eras, 
sometimes knowing of each other but more often not.  Socrates and 
Jesus, Lao Tzu and Tolstoi, Gandhi and Martin Buber -- no one can 
find in their lives and words a jot of support for a political and 
economic regime that encourages the acquisition of wealth far beyond 
what is needed for the necessaries -- or even the restorative 
pleasures -- of life while consigning the masses to live and work in squalor."
-Stephen J. Fortunato, Associate Justice, Rhode Island Supreme Court.

"Music is prophecy, its style and economic organization are ahead of 
the rest of society. It makes audible the new world that will 
gradually become visible."
-Jacques Attali in his seminal text "Noise"

Velvet Shop Logo:

~~~~~~~~~ THURSDAY - August 11th:  IN HOUSE RECORDS ~~~~~~~~~
Flyer Front: http://www.mjgamez.com/velvetshop/images/augfront_web.jpg

http://www.mjgamez.com/velvetshop/images/augback_web.jpg

One of the most well known and respected house events has been The Velvet
Shop. Created in the minds of M3, Loren, Rick Preston, and Mark Johns, The
Velvet Shop, to date has been the most successful underground platform of
the South Bay. Over the past 11 years, Mark Johns and M3 have brought in
some of the top tier DJs of the electronic music industry. Miguel Migs, Mark
Farina, David Harness, Ellen Ferrato, and Julius Papp have all graced the
tables at this venue.  Check out The Velvet Shop every Thursday at The Sofa
Lounge on 372 South First Street in Downtown San Jose.

This Thursday, August 11th The Velvet Shop proudly presents

INHOUSE RECORDS

SCOTT & NAS

AND RESIDENTS:

M3 (Green Gorilla Lounge)

MJ GAMEZ (Velvet Shop / Global Sessions)

Check out The Velvet Shop every Thursday at The Sofa Lounge on 372 South
First Street in Downtown San Jose. 9:30pm - 2am

GUEST LIST good till 10:30PM.

To get on the GUEST LIST please send email to velvetshop@mjgamez.com

After 10:30pm only 5 Bucks!

Table Reservation and Bottle Service is Available.  For reservations email
reservations@mjgamez.com

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Artists Bios / Discography:

   <http://www.mjgamez.com/velvetshop/images/m3_web.jpg>

M3  Raising the volume of the Bay Areas nightlife since the early 90s, M3
has proved himself to be an influential character in the development of the
SF/SJ house music scene. Born and raised in San Jose, M3 began his music
career in 1990 promoting some of the original Bay Areas massives such as
Get Down, Get Down, Get Down, The Gathering, and Deep Space. Initially
influenced by music ranging from Rick James, Screaming Jay Hawkins, and Led
Zepplin, M3 began his d.j. career with a smooth down-tempo sound. Since
then, his sound has evolved to include a spectrum of thumpin house beats
which he is distinctively known. His dj name, M3, initially stood for
Marijuana Motivates the Mind, but has since transformed to Makes Me Move.
M3's funky fresh style will, without a doubt, have you moving by the end of
the night.

Today, M3 keeps himself busy with event promotions, music production, and
performing. M3 is spreading the good word of house from San Francisco to San
Jose, and beyond. Playing clubs in Moscow, Spain, Prague, Paris ,
Nottingham, New York, and Hawaii, M3 is funking it up all over the world.
Closer to home, M3 focuses his time on four residencies throughout the Bay
Area which include San Joses The Velvet Shop, SFs Green Gorilla Lounge,
2nd Sundays, and Le Boom. Pairing up with the Sunset Crew, M3 also co-hosts
the not to miss Fully Loaded party every other month.

M3 has performed alongside an astounding array artists including Marshall
Jefferson, Tony Humphries, DIY Sound Systems, Derrick Carter, Cajmere, Mark
Farina, Miguel Migs, Doc Martin, Jeno, Garth, Del the Funky Homosapien, and
Rick James. M3 can be found tearing it up in the local San Francisco scene,
djing in clubs, bars, and undergrounds all over the city.

Between playing and promoting, M3 has also established his own record label,
Green Gorilla Lounge. // www.greengorillalounge.com

   <http://www.mjgamez.com/velvetshop/images/mj_web.jpg> MJ GAMEZ  MJ Gamez
(GAH-mez) is from downtown San Jose, California and began his musical career
in the late 1990's. He landed his first residency with Global Sessions Music
created by Bobby Cruz and Sergio Aragones. His anticipated sets at the Red
Room and weekly FOXY event at The Cardiff Lounge quickly caught the
attention of the house community of the Bay Area. Quickly gaining
recognition for his unique sound and ability to move a crowd in the late
hours of the evening allowed MJ to land past residencies with Team
Bluefield, NLE, Club SPY, and special guest DJ appearances at 1015 Folsom
San Francisco, Sno-Drift, Paradise Lounge, and numerous underground events
in San Francisco. To date, MJ Gamez holds residencies with the 11 year
running Velvet Shop created by M3 (Green Gorilla Lounge) and Mark Johns (The
Velvet Shop), Global Sessions Music, Karma, and Sound Palette - Sounds of
the City. MJ Gamez is the founder of the San Francisco based Sound Palette -
Sounds of the City which has been held at 1015 Folsom San Francisco and is
currently running at Sno-Drift SF. Sound Palette has brought in talent such
as JT Donaldson, Rick Preston, M3, Chris Lum, Sharon Buck, Uneaq, Justin
Martin, Pete Avila, Nikola Baytala, Sharon Buck, Roger Moorehouse, Joey
Figueroa, Ivan Bautista, and Frank Zacarias. MJ also throws a weekly event
in his own hometown on Wednesdays at the Blue Monkey Lounge called Karma.
Karma is a platform for the upcoming artists, great local talent, and
national artists to spread great house music to the South Bay.

When asked how MJ Gamez began his musical career, he smiled big and said,
"What's so beautiful about the electronic music revolution is that everyone
can distinctly remember when that revolution began for themselves. For some
it began in a room as small as my garage where the music naturally flowed to
the soul. For others it began in a huge warehouse where the music hung damp
and heavy in the air and dripped down the backs of the crowd. My revolution
was brought to life in the mid 90's by Derrick Carter and Diz with their
special guest appearances in San Francisco."

In addition to his current residencies and numerous projects MJ Gamez
actively promotes electronic music of all forms by composing articles,
literary pieces, and artwork for AM+PM Magazine (After Midnight/Post
Meridiem) and the past In The Scene Magazine. AM+PM Magazine is a New York
style mini-magazine focusing on fashion, cuisine, music and the electronic
scene of the Bay Area. In The Scene Magazine was entirely focused on the
internal and external workings of the electronic music industry. Some
featured articles include:

AM+PM Magazine:
- Watering the Dormant Roots of Electronic Music in San Jose, Volume 1
- Electronic Music Steps Out of the Shadows, Volume 2
- Dig Deep to Hear What the Scene has to Say, Volume 3
- Changing Tides for a New Season, Volume 4
- Super Club vs. The Lounge Scene, Volume 5
- TOP SECRET...new venue opening in South Bay, Volume 6
- FAHRENHEIT Ultra Lounge - After Noon. After Work. After Hours, Volume 7

When people need to get out and dance, they are satisfying a hunger deep
within to release. It's precisely that hunger that drives people to find a
particular type of music that is unique, original, and yet speaks with the
commonality we all share within. This is the music MJ Gamez brings to the
industry and is called Home Grown Music. It's a sound that is organic, full,
and native. This music gets deep inside, feels comfortable, and brings you
to that familiar place. MJ Gamez has slowly developed this sound out of the
influences Inland Nights, Chris Lum, Diz, Derrick Carter, Mark Farina, DJ
Heather, Rick Preston, JT Donaldson, Spettro, and the Lawnchair Generals.

Keep a close eye on this up and coming DJ from the west coast. His
unrelenting drive, passion for music, and love for the arts allows him to
develop new and different styles of DJing, bringing a refreshing vibe to
Northern California. His unique blend of house music is defining an
international sound that awakens the ear and causes audiences to thump with
harmony. As MJ Gamez's musical career progresses, his influences continue to
evolve and transform as he constantly drives to expose the public to
different and beautiful music. With warm sentiment MJ ended the interview
with
I ultimately want people to have that experience that causes their own
musical revolution to begin."

   <http://www.mjgamez.com/velvetshop/images/sflogo_small.jpg>

> Saturday, August 20th is the return of
>
> *[KONTROL]*
>
> minimal techno + avant house
> every 3rd Saturday at Rx Gallery
>
> featuring:
>
> *PHEEK  LIVE PA* (Montreal)
> m-nus . telegraph . contexterrior . archipel
>
> *Claude VonStroke* (San Francisco)
> dirtybird records . stepfilm
>
> plus resident DJs:
> *Sammy D* ( classic . dirtybird . utensil )
> *Alland Byallo* ( nightlight . epsionlab . mo's ferry )
> *Craig Kuna* ( concept sf . esdjco . kodo )
> *Brian Walls* ( ac . stylus . econspiracy )
>
> Digital video art by Econspiracy
>
> *Rx Gallery / 132 Eddy @ Mason, SF / 415.474.7973
> 9pm-2am / $10 / 21+ *
> Arrive early as capacity is very limited.
>
> Check out our website for photos, free music downloads, dj sets and more!
> http://www.KONTROLsf.com/ <http://www.kontrolsf.com/>
>
>
> Hailing from North America's Mecca of minimal sounds, Montreal's *Pheek* 
> has
> been blazing a brilliant path into the future of music, and gaining
> international acclaim in the process. Born Jean Patrice "JP" Remillard, in
> 1998 this lifelong music fan, early rave enthusiast, and college radio DJ
> attended a performance by Richie Hawtin/Plastikman that would forever 
> change
> his perspective on music. Inspired by this performance, he adopted the
> moniker Pheek, and within a year he was performing his own original 
> material
> live and soon released his first 12". In the six years that have followed,
> JP has been making a steady ascent to the upper echelons of the
> minimal/micro scene's most respected and innovative producers and
> performers. His style is rooted in the funky, minimal sounds of German
> tech-house, but is tempered with a heady dose of the ethereal and
> experimental, resulting in a unique sound all his own. In 2005, now with 3
> European tours, 4 full length albums and numerous acclaimed EPs on labels
> such as *Telegraph*, *Clever Music*, *Tic Tac Toe*, *Thinner*, 
> *Epsilonlab*,
> and his own *Archipel *under his belt, Pheek's talent is getting the
> worldwide recognition it deserves. This year has been an especially 
> exciting
> one for JP. After getting extensive play by DJs such as Richie Hawtin and
> Magda, Pheek was invited to contribute a track to *M-nus Records'* first
> ever compilation, *Minimize to Maximize*, and also landed an EP on Jay
> Haze's *Contexterrior* label, alongside such artists as Haze, Ricardo
> Villalobos, and Robag Wruhme. To top things off, he was invited to perform
> live at both Montreal's *MUTEK Festival*, where he played at the Finale, 
> as
> well as Detroit's *FUSE-IN Festival* (formerly the DEMF) where he 
> delivered
> an unforgettable set on the Underground Stage. Needless to say, we at
> KONTROL are hugely excited and honored to be hosting Pheek in his *first
> ever San Francisco performance*. Do not miss this one kids.
>
> *Pheek's website
> *http://www.pheek.com/index.php
>
> *Pheek's discography*
> http://www.discogs.com/artist/Pheek
>
> *Pheek LIVE @ Detroit's FUSE-IN Festival (May 2005) *
> http://www.kontrolsf.com/AUD/Pheek-LiveatFuse-In2005.mp3
>
>
> *Claude VonStroke* (better known to we locals as Barclay Crenshaw) is the
> man behind San Francisco's hottest new tech-house label, *Dirtybird 
> Records*.
> Raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Barclay eventually moved to Hollywood 
> and
> began working on feature films. Realizing that the visual medium wasn't 
> his
> calling, he moved back to downtown Detroit and fell in love with the beat.
> He began producing music and soon found a way to fuse his skills and
> experience in video with his passion for electronic music. He moved to San
> Francisco and in 2003 released *Intellect*, a six hour DVD package,
> self-directed and produced, which covered the worldwide electronic music
> scene and included interviews with the likes of Derrick May, Juan Atkins,
> Swayzak, Derrick Carter, Deep Dish, Magda, Kit Clayton and many more. In 
> SF
> Barclay met Justin and Christian Martin and Worthy and together they 
> started
> Dirtybird, with Crenshaw at the helm. The rest, as they say, is history.
> Dirtybird Records is currently shaking tailfeathers worldwide with a 
> series
> of successful releases by *Justin Martin & Sammy D* and Mr. VonStroke
> himself. With remix work by *John Tejada* and *Freaks*, and Claude's
> upcoming remixes for *Frankie*, *Jay Tripwire *, and *Justin Martin*, it's
> no mystery why the Dirtybird has taken flight and is ready to soar to
> international prominence. Bring a bar of soap, because when Claude 
> VonStroke
> is behind the decks, it's gonna get dirty.
>
> *Claude VonStroke's website*
> http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/claude_vonstroke.html
>
> *Claude VonStroke's discography*
> http://www.discogs.com/artist/Claude%20VonStroke
>
> *Claude VonStroke's dirtybird promo mix (March 2005) - "It's Time For The 
> P"

> 
> > Saturday, August 20th is the return of
> >
> > *[KONTROL]*
> >
> > minimal techno + avant house
> > every 3rd Saturday at Rx Gallery
> >
> > featuring:
> >
> > *PHEEK  LIVE PA* (Montreal)
> > m-nus . telegraph . contexterrior . archipel
> >
> > *Claude VonStroke* (San Francisco)
> > dirtybird records . stepfilm
> >
> > plus resident DJs:
> > *Sammy D* ( classic . dirtybird . utensil )
> > *Alland Byallo* ( nightlight . epsionlab . mo's
> ferry )
> > *Craig Kuna* ( concept sf . esdjco . kodo )
> > *Brian Walls* ( ac . stylus . econspiracy )
> >
> > Digital video art by Econspiracy
> >
> > *Rx Gallery / 132 Eddy @ Mason, SF / 415.474.7973
> > 9pm-2am / $10 / 21+ *
> > Arrive early as capacity is very limited.
> >
> > Check out our website for photos, free music
> downloads, dj sets and more!
> > http://www.KONTROLsf.com/
> <http://www.kontrolsf.com/>
> >
> >
> > Hailing from North America's Mecca of minimal
> sounds, Montreal's *Pheek* 
> > has
> > been blazing a brilliant path into the future of
> music, and gaining
> > international acclaim in the process. Born Jean
> Patrice "JP" Remillard, in
> > 1998 this lifelong music fan, early rave
> enthusiast, and college radio DJ
> > attended a performance by Richie Hawtin/Plastikman
> that would forever 
> > change
> > his perspective on music. Inspired by this
> performance, he adopted the
> > moniker Pheek, and within a year he was performing
> his own original 
> > material
> > live and soon released his first 12". In the six
> years that have followed,
> > JP has been making a steady ascent to the upper
> echelons of the
> > minimal/micro scene's most respected and
> innovative producers and
> > performers. His style is rooted in the funky,
> minimal sounds of German
> > tech-house, but is tempered with a heady dose of
> the ethereal and
> > experimental, resulting in a unique sound all his
> own. In 2005, now with 3
> > European tours, 4 full length albums and numerous
> acclaimed EPs on labels
> > such as *Telegraph*, *Clever Music*, *Tic Tac
> Toe*, *Thinner*, 
> > *Epsilonlab*,
> > and his own *Archipel *under his belt, Pheek's
> talent is getting the
> > worldwide recognition it deserves. This year has
> been an especially 
> > exciting
> > one for JP. After getting extensive play by DJs
> such as Richie Hawtin and
> > Magda, Pheek was invited to contribute a track to
> *M-nus Records'* first
> > ever compilation, *Minimize to Maximize*, and also
> landed an EP on Jay
> > Haze's *Contexterrior* label, alongside such
> artists as Haze, Ricardo
> > Villalobos, and Robag Wruhme. To top things off,
> he was invited to perform
> > live at both Montreal's *MUTEK Festival*, where he
> played at the Finale, 
> > as
> > well as Detroit's *FUSE-IN Festival* (formerly the
> DEMF) where he 
> > delivered
> > an unforgettable set on the Underground Stage.
> Needless to say, we at
> > KONTROL are hugely excited and honored to be
> hosting Pheek in his *first
> > ever San Francisco performance*. Do not miss this
> one kids.
> >
> > *Pheek's website
> > *http://www.pheek.com/index.php
> >
> > *Pheek's discography*
> > http://www.discogs.com/artist/Pheek
> >
> > *Pheek LIVE @ Detroit's FUSE-IN Festival (May
> 2005) *
> >
>
http://www.kontrolsf.com/AUD/Pheek-LiveatFuse-In2005.mp3
> >
> >
> > *Claude VonStroke* (better known to we locals as
> Barclay Crenshaw) is the
> > man behind San Francisco's hottest new tech-house
> label, *Dirtybird 
> > Records*.
> > Raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Barclay
> eventually moved to Hollywood 
> > and
> > began working on feature films. Realizing that the
> visual medium wasn't 
> > his
> > calling, he moved back to downtown Detroit and
> fell in love with the beat.
> > He began producing music and soon found a way to
> fuse his skills and
> > experience in video with his passion for
> electronic music. He moved to San
> > Francisco and in 2003 released *Intellect*, a six
> hour DVD package,
> > self-directed and produced, which covered the
> worldwide electronic music
> > scene and included interviews with the likes of
> Derrick May, Juan Atkins,
> > Swayzak, Derrick Carter, Deep Dish, Magda, Kit
> Clayton and many more. In 
> > SF
> > Barclay met Justin and Christian Martin and Worthy
> and together they 
> > started
> > Dirtybird, with Crenshaw at the helm. The rest, as
> they say, is history.
> > Dirtybird Records is currently shaking
> tailfeathers worldwide with a 
> > series
> > of successful releases by *Justin Martin & Sammy
> D* and Mr. VonStroke
> > himself. With remix work by *John Tejada* and
> *Freaks*, and Claude's
> > upcoming remixes for *Frankie*, *Jay Tripwire *,
> and *Justin Martin*, it's
> > no mystery why the Dirtybird has taken flight and
> is ready to soar to
> > international prominence. Bring a bar of soap,
> because when Claude 
> > VonStroke
> > is behind the decks, it's gonna get dirty.
> >
> > *Claude VonStroke's website*
> >
>
http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/claude_vonstroke.html
> >
> > *Claude VonStroke's discography*

> > P"

http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/audio/mixes/ItsTimeForTheP.mp3

Friday, August 12, 2005 ** Aquavitae: Music, Art, & Dubtribe Live! **

This is an art and music event celebrating San Francisco's creative spirit 
and cherishing the contribution that DUBTRIBE has made to our house music 
scene over the past decade+.  This *may* be their last live performance. 
See you there!!

DUBTRIBE LIVE 1-4am HESOHI LIVE 11-12am DROP CULTURE LIVE 10-11pm

8:30-9:30 Free appetizers and wine reception for the artists.  Wine 
graciously donated by Ben Gillette of Keller Estate Winery.

This event will sell out!  Buy tickets ahead of time!! Presales are 
available at Tweekin' and Skills

Online tix: http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/1970

Downstairs

8:30-10 DJ DELON 10-11 DROP CULTURE LIVE 11-12 CANYON FISHER 12-1 MELYSS 
1-2 TONIC 2-3 SMOOVE

Upstairs

10-11 J-FI 11-12 HESOHI LIVE 12-1 JASUN LOVEJOY 1-4 DUBTRIBE LIVE


Notes Bring LOVE! Be ready to get your groove on! 21 +

http://www.hyperreal.org/raves/sf/calendar2/events/view?identifier=2181 
San Francisco California, USA

Friday, August 12, 2005 ** Moxie **

MOXIE. We want to pump you up!

Moxie's the sister party to (and impetus for) the Moxie Musik radio show 
Sundays 9-11pm on WAR 93.7fm/westaddradio.com.  Enthusiasm is encouraged 
for this gathering of like-minded, hyphee boogie-mongers.  (Not 
booger-mongers, thx.)  Genres can be mis-leading, so we made our own: 
techlectro, a mish-mash of electrohaus, techno, tech-house, and (the 
über-bastard) rocktronica.

Fact is, we play fun music -- like REALLY fun -- and whatever we may be, 
we are never being boring. (We dressed up and fought, then thought: make 
amends. And we were never holding back or worried that time would come to 
an end.)  We ride the cusp of new music while pulling out those ol' gems 
and classics that express the kind of funk and synth revelry we so enjoy, 
just so we can play for you!

August 12 special DJs are Solar, Baby Ryan, Animal Style & Qzen.  So pull 
on your fun boots, and come jam with us!

More music in your pants, Moxie loves you! 
http://www.hyperreal.org/raves/sf/calendar2/events/view?identifier=2188 
San Francisco California, USA

Saturday, August 20, 2005 ** DIRTY w/Atomic Hooligan **

that's right baby.....you heard it first....Evil Breaks bringin Atomic 
Hooligan from the UK with Rhythm Method tearin it up on the outside patio.


Atomic Hooligan (Finger Lickin'/Botchit & Scarper/MOB) United Kingdom

The lads have been meddling with everything breakbeat since the early 90s. 
Matt Welch is a classically trained violinist since the age of 4 and holds 
a Masters in Music. The other Hooligan and Turntablist / Dj extraordinaire 
Terry Ryan is a graduate of the School of Audio engineering and has been 
spinning the decks since he discovered body hair. Their partnership which 
began in a club naturally, is inspiring and their brotherhood is reflected 
in their attitude towards music which is a new and refreshing one, they 
simply refuse to follow the path already walked! Evil Breaks is proud to 
have Terry Hooligan here in San Francisco for a show that is sure to be a 
memorable one.


Fire performances all night on the patio by LSD Fuego

Saturday, August 20, 2005 ** [KONTROL] presents PHEEK - LIVE + Claude 
VonStroke **

Saturday, August 20th is the return of~E

[KONTROL]

minimal techno + avant house every 3rd Saturday at Rx Gallery

featuring:

PHEEK ~V LIVE PA (Montreal) m-nus . telegraph . contexterrior . archipel

CLAUDE VonSTROKE (San Francisco) dirtybird records . stepfilm

plus resident DJs: Sammy D ( classic . dirtybird . utensil ) Alland Byallo 
( nightlight . epsionlab . mo's ferry ) Craig Kuna ( concept sf . esdjco . 
kodo ) Brian Walls ( ac . stylus . econspiracy )

Digital video art by Econspiracy

Rx Gallery / 132 Eddy @ Mason, SF / 415.474.7973 9pm-2am / $10 / 21+ 
Arrive early as capacity is very limited.

Check out our website for photos, free music downloads, dj sets and more! 
http://www.KONTROLsf.com/


Hailing from North America~Rs Mecca of minimal sounds, Montreal~Rs Pheek 
has been blazing a brilliant path into the future of music, and gaining 
international acclaim in the process.  Born Jean Patrice ~SJP~T Remillard, 
in 1998 this lifelong music fan, early rave enthusiast, and college radio 
DJ attended a performance by Richie Hawtin/Plastikman that would forever 
change his perspective on music. Inspired by this performance, he adopted 
the moniker Pheek, and within a year he was performing his own original 
material live and soon released his first 12~T. In the six years that have 
followed, JP has been making a steady ascent to the upper echelons of the 
minimal/micro scene~Rs most respected and innovative producers and 
performers.  His style is rooted in the funky, minimal sounds of German 
tech-house, but is tempered with a heady dose of the ethereal and 
experimental, resulting in a unique sound all his own.  In 2005, now with 
3 European tours, 4 full length albums and numerous acclaimed EPs on 
labels such as Telegraph, Clever Music, Tic Tac Toe, Thinner, Epsilonlab, 
and his own Archipel under his belt, Pheek~Rs talent is getting the 
worldwide recognition it deserves.  This year has been an especially 
exciting one for JP.  After getting extensive play by DJs such as Richie 
Hawtin and Magda, Pheek was invited to contribute a track to M-nus 
Records~R first ever compilation, Minimize to Maximize, and also landed an 
EP on Jay Haze~Rs Contexterrior label, alongside such artists as Haze, 
Ricardo Villalobos, and Robag Wruhme.  To top things off, he was invited 
to perform live at both Montreal~Rs MUTEK Festival, where he played at the 
Finale, as well as Detroit~Rs FUSE-IN Festival (formerly the DEMF) where 
he delivered an unforgettable set on the Underground Stage.  Needless to 
say, we at KONTROL are hugely excited and honored to be hosting Pheek in 
his first ever San Francisco performance.  Do not miss this one kids.

Pheek~Rs website http://www.pheek.com/index.php

Pheek~Rs discography http://www.discogs.com/artist/Pheek

Pheek LIVE @ Detroit~Rs FUSE-IN Festival (May 2005) 
http://www.kontrolsf.com/AUD/Pheek-LiveatFuse-In2005.mp3


Claude VonStroke (better known to we locals as Barclay Crenshaw) is the 
man behind San Francisco~Rs hottest new tech-house label, Dirtybird 
Records.  Raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Barclay eventually moved to 
Hollywood and began working on feature films.  Realizing that the visual 
medium wasn~Rt his calling, he moved back to downtown Detroit and fell in 
love with the beat.  He began producing music and soon found a way to fuse 
his skills and experience in video with his passion for electronic music. 
He moved to San Francisco and in 2003 released Intellect, a six hour DVD 
package, self-directed and produced, which covered the worldwide 
electronic music scene and included interviews with the likes of Derrick 
May, Juan Atkins, Swayzak, Derrick Carter, Deep Dish, Magda, Kit Clayton 
and many more.  In SF Barclay met Justin and Christian Martin and Worthy 
and together they started Dirtybird, with Crenshaw at the helm.  The rest, 
as they say, is history.  Dirtybird Records is currently shaking 
tailfeathers worldwide with a series of successful releases by Justin 
Martin & Sammy D and Mr. VonStroke himself. With remix work by John Tejada 
and Freaks, and Claude~Rs upcoming remixes for Frankie, Jay Tripwire, and 
Justin Martin, it~Rs no mystery why the Dirtybird has taken flight and is 
ready to soar to international prominence.  Bring a bar of soap, because 
when Claude VonStroke is behind the decks, it~Rs gonna get dirty.

Claude VonStroke~Rs website 
http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/claude_vonstroke.html

Claude VonStroke~Rs discography 
http://www.discogs.com/artist/Claude%20VonStroke

Claude VonStroke~Rs dirtybird promo mix (March 2005) - ~SIt~Rs Time For 
The P~T http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/audio/mixes/ItsTimeForTheP.mp3

Caro + [a]pendics shuffle (Live PA's) 11/19 - John Tejada + Justin Maxwell 
(Live PA's) 12/17 - Zip & Dan Bell [Perlon Tour]

Wednesday, August 24, 2005 ** Fine Cut Bodies @ Mighty **

you heard that right. The BayArea Breaks Brigade is at it again with their 
2nd party to benefit their float at this years Love Parade.



Fine Cut Bodies (Chi Recordings/Ritmic Records/Moving Target) Budapest, 
Hungary

As one of the founders of Chi Recordings, Fine Cut Bodies' tastes are 
broad and include all styles of electronic music from breaks to house to 
techno and experimental. His taste is guided more by his musical insight 
and not by any specific genre: he looks for music that is experimental but 
not selfish, interesting but not unlistenable. With the label, club night 
residencies, radio show and mixed-genre club mixes he is one of the most 
important trend-setting DJs in Hungary. Apart from appearances on the Chi 
Recordings label, Kevin has done a remix for the popular Hungarian band 
Quimby and worked on remixes for the Swiss label, Ritmic Records and the 
Dutch label, Moving Target. In the last few years, he has been a key DJ & 
promoter and has helped to develop a significant breaks scene in Hungary. 
His first 12~S titled "Deep Lack Of Balance" opened 6th on Muzik 
Magazine~Rs breaks chart and his remix for the Swiss Ritmic label called 
"The Boomspot" reached 4th on Mixmag~Rs breakbeat chart. More recently, 
Kevin's his latest release with EK & Spee, "Terminalhead", just reached 
4th on DJMag~Rs breaks & beats chart and his "Trekk Far" single was picked 
by Uberzone for the Y4K compilation on Distinctive Records and remixed by 
Elite Force. FCB's tracks are continually being supported by top-level DJs 
such as Orbital, Plump DJs, John Tejada, Mr.C, Chris Carter, Hybrid, 
Laurent Garnier and Adam Freeland. Recently, he was awarded the title of 
~SBest Hungarian Breaks DJ~T from Impulse Creator, Hungary's largest 
internet magazine and his skills behind the decks have brought him around 
the world from Europe to Australia to the United States. Currently, FCB is 
in the studio working on remixes for Tipper and Carbon Community along 
with his next EP called Versus which will consist of collaborations with 
breaks heavyweights such as Chris Carter, Hybrid and Elite Force. We are 
glad to have him back in San Francisco once again, so come out support a 
good cause, and have a wicked good time.


Along with Bayarea dj's:

Greg J (KidBippy.com/Funky Cactus/Lotek) Aaron Jae (Evil 
Breaks/SFBreaks.org/AaronJae.com) Samira (Sister SF) Mancub (Space 
Cowboys) Hypnotech (Addictech) Jay Vigor (StrategiK) Jason Who - 
Sacramento Bertzerker

Located at the world famous Mighty this show will kick off at 9pm and 
continue on till 2:30 am.

THE SFRaves.org Calendar is sent via email every week.

To subscribe to the list, send a message to: 
sfraves-calendar-subscribe@hyperreal.org

To remove your address from the list, send a message to: 
sfraves-calendar-unsubscribe@hyperreal.org

Send mail to the following for info and FAQ for this list: 
sfraves-calendar-info@hyperreal.org or sfraves-calendar-faq@hyperreal.org

If you have events to add to the SFRaves calendar, please publish them by 
Friday @ Noon to be included in the SFR Calendar Weekly Edition Mailing.

SFRaves is a not for profit entity serving the Bay Area & all forms of
electronic music for 13 years.

>Friday, August 12, 2005 ** Moxie **
>
>MOXIE. We want to pump you up!
>
>Moxie's the sister party to (and impetus for) the Moxie Musik radio show 
>Sundays 9-11pm on WAR 93.7fm/westaddradio.com.  Enthusiasm is encouraged 
>for this gathering of like-minded, hyphee boogie-mongers.  (Not 
>booger-mongers, thx.)  Genres can be mis-leading, so we made our own: 
>techlectro, a mish-mash of electrohaus, techno, tech-house, and (the 
>über-bastard) rocktronica.
>
>Fact is, we play fun music -- like REALLY fun -- and whatever we may be, we 
>are never being boring. (We dressed up and fought, then thought: make 
>amends. And we were never holding back or worried that time would come to 
>an end.)  We ride the cusp of new music while pulling out those ol' gems 
>and classics that express the kind of funk and synth revelry we so enjoy, 
>just so we can play for you!
>
>August 12 special DJs are Solar, Baby Ryan, Animal Style & Qzen.  So pull 
>on your fun boots, and come jam with us!
>
>More music in your pants, Moxie loves you! 
>http://www.hyperreal.org/raves/sf/calendar2/events/view?identifier=2188 San

>
>Atomic Hooligan (Finger Lickin'/Botchit & Scarper/MOB) United Kingdom
>
>The lads have been meddling with everything breakbeat since the early 90s. 
>Matt Welch is a classically trained violinist since the age of 4 and holds 
>a Masters in Music. The other Hooligan and Turntablist / Dj extraordinaire 
>Terry Ryan is a graduate of the School of Audio engineering and has been 
>spinning the decks since he discovered body hair. Their partnership which 
>began in a club naturally, is inspiring and their brotherhood is reflected 
>in their attitude towards music which is a new and refreshing one, they 
>simply refuse to follow the path already walked! Evil Breaks is proud to 
>have Terry Hooligan here in San Francisco for a show that is sure to be a 
>memorable one.

>Saturday, August 20, 2005 ** [KONTROL] presents PHEEK - LIVE + Claude 
>VonStroke **
>
><img src="http://www.kontrolsf.com/august/k03back.jpg" width="450" 
>height="600" border="0">
>
>
>Saturday, August 20th is the return of~E
>
>[KONTROL]
>
>minimal techno + avant house every 3rd Saturday at Rx Gallery
>
>featuring:
>
>PHEEK ~V LIVE PA (Montreal) m-nus . telegraph . contexterrior . archipel
>
>CLAUDE VonSTROKE (San Francisco) dirtybird records . stepfilm
>
>plus resident DJs: Sammy D ( classic . dirtybird . utensil ) Alland Byallo 
>( nightlight . epsionlab . mo's ferry ) Craig Kuna ( concept sf . esdjco . 
>kodo ) Brian Walls ( ac . stylus . econspiracy )
>
>Digital video art by Econspiracy
>
>Rx Gallery / 132 Eddy @ Mason, SF / 415.474.7973 9pm-2am / $10 / 21+ Arrive 
>early as capacity is very limited.
>
>Check out our website for photos, free music downloads, dj sets and more! 
>http://www.KONTROLsf.com/
>
>
>Hailing from North America~Rs Mecca of minimal sounds, Montreal~Rs Pheek 
>has been blazing a brilliant path into the future of music, and gaining 
>international acclaim in the process.  Born Jean Patrice ~SJP~T Remillard, 
>in 1998 this lifelong music fan, early rave enthusiast, and college radio 
>DJ attended a performance by Richie Hawtin/Plastikman that would forever 
>change his perspective on music. Inspired by this performance, he adopted 
>the moniker Pheek, and within a year he was performing his own original 
>material live and soon released his first 12~T. In the six years that have 
>followed, JP has been making a steady ascent to the upper echelons of the 
>minimal/micro scene~Rs most respected and innovative producers and 
>performers.  His style is rooted in the funky, minimal sounds of German 
>tech-house, but is tempered with a heady dose of the ethereal and 
>experimental, resulting in a unique sound all his own.  In 2005, now with 3 
>European tours, 4 full length albums and numerous acclaimed EPs on labels 
>such as Telegraph, Clever Music, Tic Tac Toe, Thinner, Epsilonlab, and his 
>own Archipel under his belt, Pheek~Rs talent is getting the worldwide 
>recognition it deserves.  This year has been an especially exciting one for 
>JP.  After getting extensive play by DJs such as Richie Hawtin and Magda, 
>Pheek was invited to contribute a track to M-nus Records~R first ever 
>compilation, Minimize to Maximize, and also landed an EP on Jay Haze~Rs 
>Contexterrior label, alongside such artists as Haze, Ricardo Villalobos, 
>and Robag Wruhme.  To top things off, he was invited to perform live at 
>both Montreal~Rs MUTEK Festival, where he played at the Finale, as well as 
>Detroit~Rs FUSE-IN Festival (formerly the DEMF) where he delivered an 
>unforgettable set on the Underground Stage.  Needless to say, we at KONTROL 
>are hugely excited and honored to be hosting Pheek in his first ever San 
>Francisco performance.  Do not miss this one kids.
>
>Pheek~Rs website http://www.pheek.com/index.php
>
>Pheek~Rs discography http://www.discogs.com/artist/Pheek
>
>Pheek LIVE @ Detroit~Rs FUSE-IN Festival (May 2005) 
>http://www.kontrolsf.com/AUD/Pheek-LiveatFuse-In2005.mp3
>
>
>Claude VonStroke (better known to we locals as Barclay Crenshaw) is the man 
>behind San Francisco~Rs hottest new tech-house label, Dirtybird Records.  
>Raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Barclay eventually moved to Hollywood and 
>began working on feature films.  Realizing that the visual medium wasn~Rt 
>his calling, he moved back to downtown Detroit and fell in love with the 
>beat.  He began producing music and soon found a way to fuse his skills and 
>experience in video with his passion for electronic music. He moved to San 
>Francisco and in 2003 released Intellect, a six hour DVD package, 
>self-directed and produced, which covered the worldwide electronic music 
>scene and included interviews with the likes of Derrick May, Juan Atkins, 
>Swayzak, Derrick Carter, Deep Dish, Magda, Kit Clayton and many more.  In 
>SF Barclay met Justin and Christian Martin and Worthy and together they 
>started Dirtybird, with Crenshaw at the helm.  The rest, as they say, is 
>history.  Dirtybird Records is currently shaking tailfeathers worldwide 
>with a series of successful releases by Justin Martin & Sammy D and Mr. 
>VonStroke himself. With remix work by John Tejada and Freaks, and Claude~Rs 
>upcoming remixes for Frankie, Jay Tripwire, and Justin Martin, it~Rs no 
>mystery why the Dirtybird has taken flight and is ready to soar to 
>international prominence.  Bring a bar of soap, because when Claude 
>VonStroke is behind the decks, it~Rs gonna get dirty.
>
>Claude VonStroke~Rs website 
>http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/claude_vonstroke.html
>
>Claude VonStroke~Rs discography 
>http://www.discogs.com/artist/Claude%20VonStroke
>
>Claude VonStroke~Rs dirtybird promo mix (March 2005) - ~SIt~Rs Time For The 
>P~T http://www.dirtybirdrecords.com/audio/mixes/ItsTimeForTheP.mp3

>Wednesday, August 24, 2005 ** Fine Cut Bodies @ Mighty **
>
>you heard that right. The BayArea Breaks Brigade is at it again with their 
>2nd party to benefit their float at this years Love Parade.
>
>
>
>Fine Cut Bodies (Chi Recordings/Ritmic Records/Moving Target) Budapest, 
>Hungary
>
>As one of the founders of Chi Recordings, Fine Cut Bodies' tastes are broad 
>and include all styles of electronic music from breaks to house to techno 
>and experimental. His taste is guided more by his musical insight and not 
>by any specific genre: he looks for music that is experimental but not 
>selfish, interesting but not unlistenable. With the label, club night 
>residencies, radio show and mixed-genre club mixes he is one of the most 
>important trend-setting DJs in Hungary. Apart from appearances on the Chi 
>Recordings label, Kevin has done a remix for the popular Hungarian band 
>Quimby and worked on remixes for the Swiss label, Ritmic Records and the 
>Dutch label, Moving Target. In the last few years, he has been a key DJ & 
>promoter and has helped to develop a significant breaks scene in Hungary. 
>His first 12~S titled "Deep Lack Of Balance" opened 6th on Muzik 
>Magazine~Rs breaks chart and his remix for the Swiss Ritmic label called 
>"The Boomspot" reached 4th on Mixmag~Rs breakbeat chart. More recently, 
>Kevin's his latest release with EK & Spee, "Terminalhead", just reached 4th 
>on DJMag~Rs breaks & beats chart and his "Trekk Far" single was picked by 
>Uberzone for the Y4K compilation on Distinctive Records and remixed by 
>Elite Force. FCB's tracks are continually being supported by top-level DJs 
>such as Orbital, Plump DJs, John Tejada, Mr.C, Chris Carter, Hybrid, 
>Laurent Garnier and Adam Freeland. Recently, he was awarded the title of 
>~SBest Hungarian Breaks DJ~T from Impulse Creator, Hungary's largest 
>internet magazine and his skills behind the decks have brought him around 
>the world from Europe to Australia to the United States. Currently, FCB is 
>in the studio working on remixes for Tipper and Carbon Community along with 
>his next EP called Versus which will consist of collaborations with breaks 
>heavyweights such as Chris Carter, Hybrid and Elite Force. We are glad to 
>have him back in San Francisco once again, so come out support a good 
>cause, and have a wicked good time.
>
>
>Along with Bayarea dj's:
>
